ğŸ¤ FAANG Interview Round (Professional Answers)

Q1. What is array traversal?
A: Accessing each element of an array exactly once to read or modify it.

Q2. Can arrays be traversed backwards?
A: Yes, by iterating from the last index to the first.

Q3. Is slicing the best way to reverse an array?
A: Itâ€™s concise and readable, but uses extra space.

Q4. How to reverse without extra space?
A: By swapping elements using two pointers.
